findings.suggestion:
BEFORE:
async close(): Promise<void> {
  this.db = null as unknown as lancedb.Connection
}

AFTER:
private db: lancedb.Connection | null

async close(): Promise<void> {
  this.db = null
}

WHY: Avoids the double cast escape hatch. A nullable type makes the closed state explicit and enables guard checks in other methods for better error messages.
